p2
VA musical celebration
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe cream of Vijayawada&#8217;s music world was present at Thyagaraya Gana Sabha on Saturday. Balamuralikrishna, who arrived from Chennai, led the group.He was the student of Parupalli Ramakrishnayya PanthuluSo were Annavarapu Ramaswamy and Neti Sriama Sarma. Dr. Nookala Chinna Satyanarayana, a childhood friend of Balamuralikrishna and who learnt music from his father initially, was also present.All these musicians had gathered to take part in the felicitation function organised to celebrate violin maestro Annavarapu Ramaswamy&#8217;s 83rd birthday and also conferring of the title &#8216;Nadasudhakara&#8217; by Balamuralikrishna on his disciple D. Mohanakrishna.This function was organised under the aegis of Ragavardhani Cultural Society.  Ramaswamy was Balamurali&#8217;s accompanist for maximum number of concerts.A musical atmosphere was created by Ramaswamy&#8217;s disciples, who presented vocal concerts. Janaki and Tulasi Viswanath presentedGirirajasutheof Muthiah Bhagavatar. Then they took up Dharmavati forVasama Nee Atisayamahima Telpaandgave a spirited rendition in all its facets.A popular young vocalist Modumudi Sudhakar, a scion of Parupalli family came forwardwith avarnamof his own in rareragaShruti Ranjani and rendered it as a tribute to his guru, Ramaswamy.Gayaka Sarvabhouma Varadayaka Sadguna Dhamain Lalitha and Murali&#8217;sThaayi raagatillana were his other numbers. His voice was quite forceful and emotive, matching this musical tribute.Another vocalist K. Gopala Rao too presented a brief concert.Later Annavarapu was warmly felicitated by Balamuralikrishna, Nookala Chinna Satyanarayana and others. Animal Husbandry Minister Mandali Buddha Prasadjoined the function and spoke about Balamuralikrishna&#8217;s and Nookala&#8217;s contribution to music.
